cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a method for distributed signal processing in wireless sensor networks, which involves cluster analysis and feature extraction. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Among these, cs.MA and cs.NI are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of distributed signal processing in wireless networks. However, the paper also discusses numerical experiments and applications in computer vision, which could make cs.CV a relevant category as well. Finally, the use of gravitational force as a metaphor for clustering suggests a potential connection to cs.SY and control theory.
